    en: "A Notice of Pendency, also called a lis pendens, is a document filed with the County Clerk under CPLR 6501 that warns the world that a lawsuit is pending affecting the title, use, or possession of a specific parcel of real estate. Once filed and indexed, it binds every subsequent purchaser, lender, or lienor as if they were a party to the lawsuit. The notice is extremely powerful — a seller cannot close on a sale free and clear until the lis pendens is either released or the underlying case is resolved. CPLR 6514 gives the court authority to cancel a wrongly filed lis pendens, and a defendant can recover costs and attorney's fees under CPLR 6514(c) for a cancelled filing made without probable cause."
